post_text:
As you may have heard, Mr. Travis was nominated by a few students and was awarded the WGN Teacher of the Month for March -- so well deserved and we are so proud of him!

His segment will air tomorrow, Thursday, 5/28 on WGN during the 9 P.M. news.

All of you that know Mr. Travis knows that he is an awesome teacher, a role model to his peers, a leader in our district, and the guy who knows everything about tech and music and on and on... We are so glad to know that he has been recognized in this way.

So tomorrow, please tune in to WGN at 9 p.m. to view his segment and join us in celebrating him.

Our community and school is so lucky to have him.

post_text: Students from Franzen and Peacock created inspirational sidewalk chalk art, positive word graffiti posters, inspirational words using materials from nature and painted inspirational rocks. Some students also created posters and lawn signs (donated by Tree Guys Pizza) that included a positive phrase and background. They were shared and posted at businesses throughout the community. We hope their art will uplift you and unite us all as a group during this challenging time. #weareitasca10

--------------

District 10 Parent/Guardians,

We hope this letter finds you well! Thank you for your continued At Home Learning efforts and support the past few weeks. We would like your feedback to help us better understand and plan for At Home Learning now that we have experienced this new way of teaching and learning for some time.

At-Home Learning Parent/Guardian Survey: https://forms.gle/M67rFoPoJszZSs528

Please complete one survey per family. We appreciate your time and look forward to using the results to support students, teachers, and staff.

Stay safe and be well,

District 10 Administration Team

_____

Dear Itasca 10 Families,

Please note that today Governor Pritzker extended the stay-at-home order through the month of April. This means that Home Learning will continue through April 30th. We are hopeful that schools might resume on May 1st.

Please stay safe, stay home and maintain social distancing when interacting with others.

We appreciate all of the support, patience, and flexibility during this time.

Stay safe and be well,

D10 Administration Team

Itasca School District 10 is offering breakfast and lunch services for all children living in the community during school closure. Lunches will be delivered on Monday, March 30th and Thursday, April 6th from 9 a.m.- 11:00 a.m. If you are in need of these services please indicate on the form linked here https://forms.gle/ME5Lp7Uenc88AxpH6

If you already receive free lunch or have already filled out the survey you do not need to do this again, however if you would like to be added please do so at your earliest convenience.

Lunch and Breakfast Service Survey
text:
Itasca School District 10 is offering breakfast and lunch services for all children living in the community during school closure. Lunches will be delivered on Monday, March 30th and Thursday, April 6th from 9 a.m.- 11:00 a.m. If you are in need of these services please indicate on the form linked here https://forms.gle/ME5Lp7Uenc88AxpH6

If you already receive free lunch or have already filled out the survey you do not need to do this again, however if you would like to be added please do so at your earliest convenience.
